  <num>29-6270</num>
  <heading>INDEPENDENT LIVING SKILLS (ยง 29-6270)</heading>
  <level>
    <num>6270.1.</num>
    <text>As early as practicable, but no later than a resident&amp;#8217;s fourteenth (14th) birthday, the facility shall develop and follow a written plan to teach independent living skills that are individualized, age-appropriate, and in accordance with
      each resident&amp;#8217;s ISP, including knowledge, practices and skills in the following areas:</text>
    <level>
      <num>(a)</num>
      <text>General health, general safety and fire safety;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(b)</num>
      <text>Reproductive health and contraception;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(c)</num>
      <text>Parenting skills, including child development, health, and safety;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(d)</num>
      <text>HIV and sexually transmitted disease;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(e)</num>
      <text>Problem solving and decision-making;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(f)</num>
      <text>Conflict resolution, negotiation, team building, peer support, and relationship;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(g)</num>
      <text>Work readiness and employment;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(h)</num>
      <text>Stress reduction;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(i)</num>
      <text>Money management;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(j)</num>
      <text>Meal purchase, preparation and storage;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(k)</num>
      <text>Nutrition;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(l)</num>
      <text>Shopping;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(m)</num>
      <text>Personal grooming and hygiene;</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(n)</num>
      <text>Transportation; and</text>
    </level>
    <level>
      <num>(o)</num>
      <text>Household maintenance.</text>
    </level>
  </level>
